external_knowledge:
- 'Musical treasures' refers to the titles of albums;
- 'Guardians' refers to the artists;
- 'Ocean they swim in' refers to the genre of the albums;
- 'Vast sea of Rock' refers to the genre named 'Rock'.

- "last couple of decades" refers to after the year 2000;
- "diverse styles" means the number of different genres an artist has albums in;
- "total lengths of their musical works" refers to the sum of the lengths of their albums;
- "where these versatile musicians are from" indicates the origin of the artists.

sql:
SELECT albums.title, album_reviews.rating
FROM albums
JOIN album_reviews ON albums.album_id = album_reviews.album_id;

SELECT DISTINCT artists.artist_name
FROM albums
INNER JOIN artists ON albums.artist_id = artists.artist_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Shining stars from the American shores" represents artists who originate from the USA;
- "Shimmered the music world" indicates the release of albums in the specified time period;
- "Radiant album titles" correspond to the titles of albums;
- "Starlight rating" is a metaphor for the user ratings on a 1 to 5 scale;
- "Average starlight rating above 4.5" implies the condition `AVG(album_reviews.rating) > 4.5`.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM albums 
WHERE release_date >= '2000-01-01';

SELECT MAX(album_count) as max_album_count
FROM (
  SELECT artist_id, COUNT(*) as album_count
  FROM albums
  GROUP BY artist_id
) as subquery;
